---

## Firebase Structure

coaches (collection)
  {coachId}
    name, email, school
    players (subcollection)
      {playerId} - name, age, className, position, parentName, parentPhone, status, coachNotes
    sessions (subcollection)
      {sessionId} - name, time, location, focus, dateMillis, status
        attendance (subcollection)
          {playerId} - playerName, isPresent
        performance (subcollection)
          {perfId} - playerName, points, assists, rebounds, effort, defense

---

## Setup & Installation

1. Clone the repository
   git clone https://github.com/yourusername/CoachPro-Android.git

2. Firebase Setup
   - Go to console.firebase.google.com
   - Create a new project
   - Add Android app with package name: com.example.coachpro
   - Download google-services.json and paste inside app/ folder
   - Enable Firebase Authentication (Email/Password)
   - Enable Cloud Firestore (Test mode)

3. Firestore Composite Index
   - Collection : sessions
   - Field      : dateMillis - Ascending
   - Scope      : Collection

4. Run the app
   Open in Android Studio and click Run

---

## Modules Overview

Module        Screens                      Firebase
----------    -------------------------    ----------------
Auth          Login, Register              Firebase Auth
Dashboard     DashboardFragment            Firestore Read
Players       PlayersList, Add, Detail     CRUD
Sessions      SessionsList, Add, Detail    CRUD
Attendance    AttendanceActivity           Batch Write
Performance   PerformanceList, Add         CRUD
Profile       ProfileFragment              Read + Auth Sign Out

